{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# WS6-a â€” Gerrit LLM-Review voter integration (voter + REST vote + stub-Gerrit tests)\n\n## Why\nThe code-review capability (WS1â€“WS5) must be wired as the Gerrit `LLM-Review` voter: on\n`patchset-created`, run the four-pass gate over the change and vote `LLM-Review` via Gerrit REST,\nwith the deterministic block/advisory outcome mapping to the label. This story is the **codeable +\nstub-testable** deliverable (deliverable *a*): the adapter seam, vote-mapping, REST client, and\npatchset handler, all verifiable against a STUB Gerrit â€” before any live environment. The live\nend-to-end dogfood proof is split into WS6-b (blocked on the deployed AWS/Gerrit env).\n\n## What\n- `src/rebar/gerrit/` â€” a new package: the `code_review_decision` adapter over\n  `produce_code_review_verdict`, a Gerrit REST client (diff-fetch + vote), a patchset-created\n  handler, and the staged opt-in + rollback config.\n- ADR 0013 capturing the voter architecture (see AC7).\n- Everything is exercised offline against a stub Gerrit client (no network).\n\n## Scope\n- IN: the voter integration (adapter seam + vote-mapping + REST diff-fetch + REST vote + patchset\n  handler + staged opt-in/rollback config + review-message vocabulary) + ADR 0013 + its offline\n  stub-Gerrit tests.\n- OUT: the live dogfood proof (WS6-b, gated on the deployed env); the capability itself (WS1â€“WS5);\n  the CI \"Verified\" second vote (epic 1fa8); provisioning the `LLM-Review` label / submit\n  requirement / service-account (provisioned by d251 â€” this story CONSUMES them).\n\n## The adapter seam (the d251-S4b contract)\n`code_review_decision(diff_text: str, repo_root: str, ref: str | None) -> dict` wraps\n`produce_code_review_verdict` (WS4) and returns a receiver-stable shape:\n`{decision: \"PASS\"|\"BLOCK\", label_value: int, coverage_gap: bool, message: str}`. The d251\nreceiver consumes only `decision`/`label_value`/`message`; WS6-b's live receiver does not change\non swap.\n\n**Gate-enable override (critical):** `produce_code_review_verdict` internally consults\n`code_review_enabled(repo_root)`, which reads `verify.enable_code_review` from the *reviewed\nrepo's* `rebar.toml` â€” a flag that defaults to `false`. If the adapter did nothing, the voter\nwould receive the inert disabled verdict on essentially every change and fail-closed to `-1`\nforever. So when invoked by the voter, the adapter **forces the gate enabled**: since\n`enable_code_review` is a `VerifyConfig`/repo-config field read via `code_review_enabled(repo_root)`\n(NOT an `LLMConfig` field â€” an `LLMConfig` override would not flip it), the mechanism is an\nexplicit enablement override â€” `produce_code_review_verdict` gains an optional `enabled: bool |\nNone = None` parameter that, when set, bypasses the `code_review_enabled(repo_root)` config read;\nthe voter passes `enabled=True`. **Voter activation via `[gerrit_voter]` + allowlist is already the\nauthoritative gate**, so the per-repo flag is a redundant second gate in this context. The inert-disabledâ†’coverage-gap mapping below is retained purely as\ndefense-in-depth (if the override is ever absent, an inert PASS still never becomes a submittable\n`+MAX`). A test asserts the voter fires (reviews + votes) even when the reviewed repo has no\n`rebar.toml` / has `enable_code_review=false`.\n\n## Vote mapping (exact integers; all three verdicts covered)\n`produce_code_review_verdict` emits **three** verdicts â€” PASS, BLOCK, **INDETERMINATE** (LLM\noutage/degradation, or a fail-closed security abstain). The adapter collapses them to a two-value\ndecision, fail-closed. Note `produce_code_review_verdict` also returns an **INERT disabled-path\nverdict** (`verdict==PASS` but `coverage.enabled==false`) when `verify.enable_code_review` is\nfalse â€” this MUST NOT become a submittable `+MAX` (that would let an unreviewed change merge). It\nis treated as a coverage-gap, fail-closed:\n\n| verdict / state | decision | `LLM-Review` vote | note |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| PASS + `coverage.enabled==true` (advisory findings allowed) | PASS | `+MAX` | advisory findings surfaced in the message but do NOT lower the vote |\n| BLOCK (blocking findings) | BLOCK | `-1` | real finding |\n| INDETERMINATE (LLM outage / degraded) | BLOCK | `-1` | **fail-closed** coverage-gap |\n| PASS but `coverage.enabled==false` (gate disabled) | BLOCK | `-1` | **fail-closed** coverage-gap (`gate-disabled`) â€” an inert PASS is never certified |\n\nThere is no `+1` case (the earlier `+1/MAX` notation is removed as ambiguous): a change either\nclears review (`+MAX`) or is vetoed (`-1`). `label_value` is resolved against the label's\nprovisioned MAX (config `gerrit_voter.max_vote`, default 1) so a `LLM-Review -1..+1` and a\n`-2..+2` label are both supported without code change.\n\n**`coverage_gap` derivation (exact):** `coverage_gap = (not coverage.get(\"enabled\", False)) or\ncoverage.get(\"llm_unavailable\", False) or any(n.get(\"reason\") == \"fail-closed-abstain\" for n in\ncoverage.get(\"security_detectors\", []))`. `coverage_gap` is True for the three fail-closed rows\nabove (gate-disabled, llm-unavailable, scanner-abstain) and drives the coverage-gap message tag;\na BLOCK from a real finding has `coverage_gap=False`.\n\n## Event delivery + `repo_root` acquisition\n- **Event mechanism:** the handler is triggered by Gerrit's **`webhooks` plugin** (an HTTP POST of\n  the `patchset-created` event to the rebar-MCP receiver URL) â€” chosen over the `hooks` plugin\n  (requires local script execution on the Gerrit host â€” wrong topology for a remote MCP\n  receiver), SSH `stream-events` (a long-lived daemon connection â€” more operational surface), and\n  REST polling (no push, latency + wasted calls). d251 provisions the webhook config. The handler\n  itself is written mechanism-AGNOSTIC â€” it takes a parsed `{project, change_id, revision_id,\n  ref}` event object â€” so `stream-events` is a drop-in alternative wiring without touching the\n  handler/adapter.\n- **`repo_root`:** the security detectors (WS5) scan the CHANGED FILES at `repo_root`, so the\n  change content must be on disk. To avoid a concurrent-patchset race on a shared per-project\n  checkout, the handler materializes a **per-revision ephemeral checkout** (a `git worktree` /\n  temp checkout keyed by `revision_id`) under `gerrit_voter.checkout_root`, fetches the event\n  `ref` into it, passes it as `repo_root`, and removes it after voting. Concurrent events on the\n  same project therefore never share mutable working state. For the offline stub tests, `repo_root`\n  is a temp dir (the stub serves a canned diff; the gate runs over the provided `diff_text`).\n\n## Gerrit REST API surface (concrete endpoints + auth)\nThe client speaks the authenticated Gerrit REST API under the `/a/` path. All JSON responses\nstrip Gerrit's `)]}'` XSSI prefix before parsing.\n- **Diff fetch** (patchset handler, live only): `GET /a/changes/{change-id}/revisions/{revision-id}/patch`\n  returns the base64-encoded unified diff â†’ decode to `diff_text`. Changed files:\n  `GET /a/changes/{change-id}/revisions/{revision-id}/files` (keys are the changed paths) â€” or\n  derive from the unified diff.\n- **Diff-fetch failure** (distinct earlier sub-step): a `GET /patch` or `/files` that fails\n  (404/401/5xx/timeout, after the same transient-retry/fail-fast policy) means the change cannot\n  be reviewed â†’ **fail-closed**: post `-1` with the coverage-gap sub-reason `diff-unavailable`\n  (the adapter is never called; there is nothing to certify). If that `-1` post ALSO fails, the\n  vote-failure path applies (no vote â†’ change held un-submittable). A stub-driven test covers a\n  diff-fetch failure analogous to the vote-POST-failure test.\n- **Vote + message** (SetReview): `POST /a/changes/{change-id}/revisions/{revision-id}/review`\n  with a `ReviewInput` JSON body: `{\"labels\": {\"LLM-Review\": <label_value>}, \"message\": \"<tag +\n  summary>\"}`. The vote comment is posted as the top-level `ReviewInput.message` (the change-level\n  review message), NOT Gerrit's formal per-line `robot_comments` field â€” the first-line tag makes\n  it machine-parseable without a `robotId`/`robotRunId` contract. (File/line-anchored\n  `robot_comments` are a documented OPTIONAL enhancement, out of scope for v1.)\n- **Auth:** HTTP Basic against `/a/` using the service account's Gerrit **HTTP-password**\n  credential (username + generated HTTP password, provisioned by d251), base64-encoded in the\n  `Authorization: Basic â€¦` header â€” the same transport posture as the reconciler's `acli_rest`.\n\n## Staged opt-in + rollback (the config gate)\nBecause a receiver processes Gerrit projects generically (not rebar's own repo_root), voter\nactivation is a **receiver-level** config, NOT the per-repo `verify.enable_code_review`:\n\n- New config section `[gerrit_voter]` (in the rebar-MCP receiver's `rebar.toml`; env overrides\n  `REBAR_GERRIT_VOTER_ENABLED`, `REBAR_GERRIT_VOTER_PROJECTS`):\n  - `enabled: bool = false` â€” the **master kill-switch** (rollback): `false` disables the voter\n    entirely regardless of the allowlist. Safe default OFF.\n  - `enabled_projects: list[str] = []` â€” the per-project **allowlist** of Gerrit project names. A\n    project is active iff `enabled AND (project in enabled_projects OR \"*\" in enabled_projects)`.\n    Empty list â‡’ no project active (safe default). `\"*\"` is the documented **fleet-wide** toggle.\n  - `max_vote: int = 1` â€” the label's provisioned MAX (see vote mapping).\n  - `label: str = \"LLM-Review\"` â€” the Gerrit label name to vote on (config, not hardcoded, so a\n    differently-named label needs no code change).\n  - `checkout_root: str` â€” base path for the per-project local checkouts the handler reviews.\n- **Lifecycle/ownership:** the config is a PR-gated file in the rebar-MCP deployment repo (single\n  reviewed source, no ad-hoc mutation). Adding a project = a reviewed PR appending to\n  `enabled_projects`; **retiring** one = removing it; **rollback** = flip `enabled=false` (or drop\n  the project). Disabling stops FUTURE votes; existing votes are left in place (Gerrit's\n  `copyCondition`, provisioned by d251, governs vote carry/reset across patchsets).\n- An inactive project (voter off / not allow-listed) â‡’ the handler returns WITHOUT voting (no\n  side effect), so activation is genuinely staged.\n\n## Review-message vocabulary (fail-closed vs real-finding distinction)\nEvery vote posts a `ReviewInput.message` whose FIRST line is a machine-parseable tag so an\ninfra-failure `-1` is unmistakable from a real-finding `-1`:\n- `[LLM-Review: PASS]` â€” `+MAX`.\n- `[LLM-Review: BLOCK â€” finding]` â€” a real blocking finding (`coverage_gap==False`) â†’ `-1`.\n- `[LLM-Review: BLOCK â€” coverage-gap (<reason>)]` â€” a **fail-closed** `-1` (`coverage_gap==True`),\n  where `<reason>` is one of `gate-disabled` (`enable_code_review` off â€” should not occur given the\n  force-enable override; defense-in-depth), `llm-unavailable` (LLM outage), `scanner` (a\n  `fail-closed-abstain` security detector â€” the message names which scanner), or `diff-unavailable`\n  (the Gerrit diff-fetch failed). The message tells an operator to \"re-enable/re-run when infra is\n  healthy,\" not \"your code is bad.\"\nThe tag + sub-reason vocabulary is a documented constant (`gerrit.voter.MESSAGE_TAGS`) with a test\nasserting each row (PASS, finding, and each coverage-gap sub-reason).\n\n## REST vote failure behavior (non-happy path)\nThe Gerrit REST client mirrors the reconciler's transport posture\n(`_engine/rebar_reconciler/acli_rest.py`): urllib + Basic Auth (service-account token provisioned\nby d251), **retry on transient faults** (timeout / connection reset) with bounded backoff,\n**fail-fast on deterministic HTTP errors** (4xx/5xx â€” no retry). Outcomes:\n- Vote POST ultimately fails (network/auth/5xx after retries) â‡’ the handler logs the error and\n  returns a distinct `VoteError` result; **no `LLM-Review` vote is recorded**. This is safe: with\n  no `+MAX`, d251's `=MAX` submit requirement holds the change un-submittable (fail-closed by\n  construction â€” a missing vote never lets an unreviewed change merge).\n- The gate itself errors/times out (not the REST call) â‡’ `produce_code_review_verdict` already\n  degrades to INDETERMINATE â‡’ decision=BLOCK â‡’ `-1` + a `coverage-gap` robot comment (above).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `src/rebar/gerrit/` implements `code_review_decision(diff_text, repo_root, ref) -> {decision, label_value, coverage_gap, message}` over `produce_code_review_verdict`; the d251 receiver consumes only `decision`/`label_value`/`message` (seam test pins the shape). `coverage_gap` uses the exact derivation above.\n- [ ] Vote mapping is exhaustive over PASS/BLOCK/INDETERMINATE **and the inert disabled-path verdict**: PASS(enabled)â†’`+MAX`; BLOCKâ†’`-1`; INDETERMINATEâ†’`-1`; PASS-but-`coverage.enabled==false`â†’`-1` (fail-closed, `gate-disabled`) â€” an inert PASS is NEVER a submittable `+MAX`. A test asserts each state â†’ the correct integer (no `+1` case; advisory findings keep `+MAX`).\n- [ ] A patchset-created handler fetches the change diff via `GET /a/changes/{id}/revisions/{rev}/patch` (+ `.../files`), calls the adapter, and votes `LLM-Review` via `POST /a/changes/{id}/revisions/{rev}/review` (`ReviewInput{labels,message}`) â€” verified END-TO-END against a **stub Gerrit** (no network); the stub records the posted `{labels, message}` and serves the canned diff.\n- [ ] Staged opt-in: `[gerrit_voter]` config (`enabled` master kill-switch default false; `enabled_projects` allowlist, `\"*\"` = fleet-wide; `max_vote`); a project is active only when `enabled AND allow-listed`; an inactive project â‡’ handler returns WITHOUT voting. Config schema + lifecycle/rollback documented; a test pins the active/inactive gate.\n- [ ] The review message distinguishes a fail-closed/coverage-gap `-1` (sub-reason `gate-disabled` / `llm-unavailable` / `scanner` / `diff-unavailable`) from a real-finding `-1`, via the documented first-line tag vocabulary; a test asserts the PASS tag, the finding tag, and each coverage-gap sub-reason.\n- [ ] REST-vote failure behavior: retry on transient (timeout/connection), fail-fast on 4xx/5xx; a vote POST that ultimately fails yields a distinct error result and records NO vote (change stays un-submittable â€” fail-closed); a stub-driven test asserts this.\n- [ ] Diff-fetch failure behavior: a `GET /patch`/`/files` that fails â‡’ the handler posts `-1` with the `coverage-gap (diff-unavailable)` tag WITHOUT calling the adapter (fail-closed); a stub-driven test asserts this (analogous to the vote-POST-failure test).\n- [ ] The adapter forces `enable_code_review=True` when the voter invokes it (voter activation is the authoritative gate); a test asserts the voter reviews + votes even when the reviewed repo has `enable_code_review=false` / no `rebar.toml`.\n- [ ] An ADR (0013) captures the Gerrit voter architecture: the `code_review_decision` seam contract, the concrete Gerrit REST endpoints + auth, the vote-mapping (incl. INDETERMINATE + inert-disabled fail-closed), the staged opt-in/rollback config, the review-message vocabulary, and the REST-failure posture.\n\n## Dependencies\n- CONSUMES d251's provisioned artifacts (label, submit requirement, copyCondition, service\n  account) â€” but this story's code + stub tests do NOT require the live env. The live proof is\n  WS6-b.\n- depends_on WS4 (98ff, closed) for `produce_code_review_verdict`.\n\n## Plan-review remediation (2026-06-30, Round-13)\n- BLOCK (config underspecified Ă—2): specified the `[gerrit_voter]` receiver-level config â€” format,\n  location, data model, master kill-switch, allowlist semantics, `\"*\"` fleet-wide, lifecycle,\n  ownership, retirement, rollback.\n- Advisory (split): split the dogfood into WS6-b (blocked on the live env); this story is\n  deliverable *a* only, closeable now.\n- Advisory (INDETERMINATE): added to the vote-mapping table + AC as a fail-closed `-1`.\n- Advisory (vote ambiguity): removed `+1/MAX`; exact integers stated (`+MAX` / `-1`).\n- Advisory (REST failure, rollback, robot-comment vocab, stub-test AC, ADR): each now has a\n  dedicated section + AC.\n\n## Plan-review remediation (2026-06-30, Round-14)\n- BLOCK (disabled-gate â†’ inert PASS): the adapter now treats an inert disabled-path verdict\n  (`coverage.enabled==false`) as a fail-closed coverage-gap `-1` (`gate-disabled`) â€” an inert PASS\n  is never a submittable `+MAX`. Added to the vote-mapping table + AC2 + the `coverage_gap`\n  derivation.\n- Critical (no REST endpoints / diff-fetch / robot_comments / auth): added the \"Gerrit REST API\n  surface\" section pinning the diff-fetch (`.../revisions/{rev}/patch` + `.../files`), the vote\n  (`POST .../review` with `ReviewInput{labels,message}`), the `message`-vs-`robot_comments` choice\n  (message field; structured robot_comments an optional enhancement), and HTTP-password Basic auth\n  on `/a/`.\n- Advisory (coverage_gap derivation): stated the exact boolean rule.\n- Advisory (ADR in body): ADR 0013 now named in What/Scope, not only AC7.\n- Advisory (7 ACs / â‰Ą4 components): kept as ONE story â€” the adapter/REST/handler/config are a\n  single tightly-coupled package built + stub-tested together (~300â€“400 LOC); further splitting\n  would fragment one cohesive unit and its shared stub harness. Judged not worth a split.\n\n## Plan-review remediation (2026-06-30, Round-15 â€” advisories on a PASSing review)\n- Critical (permanent fail-closed): the adapter now **force-enables** the gate\n  (`enable_code_review=True`) since voter activation is the authoritative gate; the\n  inert-disabledâ†’`-1` mapping is retained only as defense-in-depth. Added an AC + test (voter fires\n  with no `rebar.toml`).\n- Major (repo_root acquisition): specified â€” per-project local checkout under\n  `gerrit_voter.checkout_root`, the handler fetches the event `ref`.\n- Major (event mechanism): specified the `webhooks` plugin (justified vs hooks/stream-events/\n  polling); the handler is mechanism-agnostic (parsed event object).\n- Major Ă—2 (diff-fetch failure): added the `diff-unavailable` coverage-gap `-1` path + an AC +\n  a stub test.\n- Minor (label hardcoded): `gerrit_voter.label` config.\n- Minor (deploy ordering): the voter code ships first (inert until `[gerrit_voter].enabled=true`);\n  d251's label/submit-requirement/service-account must exist before activation â€” captured in ADR\n  0013.\n\n## Plan-review remediation (2026-06-30, Round-16 â€” mechanism accuracy on a PASSing review)\n- Critical (force-enable mechanically impossible as stated): corrected â€” `enable_code_review` is a\n  repo-config field read via `code_review_enabled(repo_root)`, so the override is an explicit\n  `enabled: bool|None` parameter added to `produce_code_review_verdict` (bypasses the config read),\n  NOT an `LLMConfig` field. The voter passes `enabled=True`.\n- Major (shared-checkout concurrent-event race): corrected â€” a per-revision ephemeral checkout\n  (git worktree keyed by `revision_id`), removed after voting; concurrent events never share\n  mutable state.\n- Minor (AC5 omitted `diff-unavailable`): added.\n- Remaining advisories (credential wording token-vs-HTTP-password, checkout retirement path) are\n  live-deployment concerns folded into WS6-b / ADR 0013, and precise HTTP-password Basic-auth is\n  already specified in the REST-surface section. Not re-looping the review â€” the plan PASSES; these\n  are code/ADR-level details captured at implementation."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782866630128242001,"uuid":"1bc5a968-9a6d-495f-9803-18f6d8f21bcb"}